other_tests.procedure_name: Ultrasound of the Liver or Gallbladder
other_tests.findings: The liver is normal in shape and contour with no focal hepatic lesions. There is a small amount of pneumobilia, normal portal vein flow, no biliary duct dilation, and multiple large gallstones with a thickened gallbladder wall measuring up to 5 mm. No gallbladder wall edema or pericholecystic fluid is noted.
